---
description: Before controller redeploy, require commit and push in current repository.
alwaysApply: true
---

- Controller redeploy gate (MUST):
  - Before the controller is redeployed, the required changes MUST be committed AND the commit MUST be pushed
    to the remote of the current repository.
  - Commit message MUST be minimal plain text, without any additional tags/trailers/labels.
  - Do NOT redeploy the controller if commit or push has not been completed.

- Who does what (MUST):
  - The agent may create the commit when the user asks it to commit.
  - The agent MUST NOT `git push` unless the user has explicitly asked for a push in this conversation. This
    rule is a redeploy PRECONDITION, not a standing authorization to push. "Commit" does not imply "push".
  - Default flow: the agent commits, then STOPS and asks the user to push and redeploy (or asks for explicit
    permission to push). Only when the user explicitly authorizes a push may the agent run `git push`.
  - The agent only performs the redeploy itself when the user explicitly asks it to; in that case it must first
    ensure commit+push are done (asking the user to push, or pushing only with explicit permission).
